description:
Marvel's relaunch of The Amazing Spider-Man Vol.1 after issue #441. After issue #30 (#471) Marvel used a dual numbering system, yet the indicia still stated The Amazing Spider-Man Vol. 2. The series ran for 58 issues until it's 40th anniversary where it resumed it's legacy numbering with issue #500, returning as The Amazing Spider-Man Vol.1.

Collected Editions

  • Spider-Man: The Gathering of Five (#440-441)
  • Coming Home (#471-476)
  • Revelations (#477-480)
  • Until the Stars Turn Cold (#481-486)
  • Life and Death of Spiders (#487-491)
  • Unintended Consequences (#492-497)
  • Happy Birthday (#498-502)

Issue's #30-58 have been translated into Spanish.
name: The Amazing Spider-Man

deck: A dark children's book and graphic novel.
description:
The Squickerwonkers is a dark children's book and the first graphic novel by Canadian actress Evangeline Lilly (LOST, The Hobbit) with illustrations by New Zealander sculpture Johnny Frasier-Allen (Peter Jackson's King Kong and The Hobbit trilogy). It is published by Titan Books.

In interviews promoting the release of the book, Evangeline Lilly said The Squickerwonkers is planned to be a series of many graphic novels (two different series of nine books apiece) further exploring the Squickerwonkers universe. Lilly also mentioned that she has been thinking and writing about The Squickerwonkers since her childhood. She wrote the first poem (also The Squickerwonkers) at the age of fourteen, in 1994.
name: The Squickerwonkers
